b'@CNBCFastMoney @MelissaLeeCNBC a few months ago one of the @CNBC shows had  an analyst say $INSP was his best short idea. The stock is up around 60% since then. The TAM of 17.6 million people with moderate to severe sleep apnea and an invasive surgery makes me question the 5'

b'In late \'99 there were tech "inevitables" like $MSFT, $INTC, $CSCO. Late cycle, traders got bored with those and jumped into the more "exciting" stocks like $JDSU, $ISLD, $INSP. It feels similar now. $GOOG, $FB, $MSFT, $AMZN are not interesting compared to the "real winners".'
